<component id="ID_txt03">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>The Internet is divided up into collections of networks called autonomous systems.</li><br/><li>Within an autonomous system, interior gateway routing protocols are used, such as RIP, EIGRP and OSPF.</li><br/><li>Between autonomous systems, exterior gateway routing functions are required. Exterior Gateway Protocols (EGPs) run on exterior routers, or border gateways, that are located at the border of an AS. The most common EGP is Border Gateway Protocol (BGP).</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>

